    "94": "ZP indirect pointer lo — movement grid for BFS pathfinding. Lo=$2B, hi ($5F) = current page ($67..$7F). Used as (ptr_move_grid_lo),Y by update_guard_pathfinding to test passability bits.",
    "96": "Lo byte of ZP indirect pointer ptr_pathfinding_lo/$61. Always $55 (constant column offset into attr RAM page). Hi byte ($61) = guard_page+1 per slot. Used as lda (ptr_pathfinding_lo),y in apply_pathfinding_to_guards to read BFS direction code.",
    "97": "Hi byte of ZP indirect pointer p60/$61. Set to guard_page+1 each iteration of apply_pathfinding_to_guards. Together with p60=$55 (lo), forms pointer to guard's pathfinding attr RAM row for lda (p60),y dispatch.",
